get.description: Retrieves the list of accounts, possibly filtered.

parameters.name: active
parameters.description: Select only active accounts. Dont set this field to select both active and non-active accounts.

parameters.name: ids
parameters.description: Select only accounts with these IDs.

parameters.name: maxResults
parameters.description: Maximum number of results to return.

parameters.name: pageToken
parameters.description: Value of the nextPageToken from the previous result page.

parameters.name: profileId
parameters.description: User profile ID associated with this request.

parameters.name: searchString
parameters.description: Allows searching for objects by name or ID. Wildcards (*) are allowed. For example, account*2015 will return objects with names like account June 2015, account April 2015, or simply account 2015. Most of the searches also add wildcards implicitly at the start and the end of the search string. For example, a search string of account will match objects with name my account, account 2015, or simply account.

parameters.name: sortField
parameters.description: Field by which to sort the list.

parameters.name: sortOrder
parameters.description: Order of sorted results, default is ASCENDING.

parameters.description: Select only active ads.

parameters.name: campaignIds
parameters.description: Select only ads with these campaign IDs.

parameters.name: compatibility
parameters.description: Select default ads with the specified compatibility. Applicable when type is AD_SERVING_DEFAULT_AD. WEB and WEB_INTERSTITIAL refer to rendering either on desktop or on mobile devices for regular or interstitial ads, respectively. APP and APP_INTERSTITIAL are for rendering in mobile apps. IN_STREAM_VIDEO refers to rendering an in-stream video ads developed with the VAST standard.

parameters.name: dynamicClickTracker
parameters.description: Select only dynamic click trackers. Applicable when type is AD_SERVING_CLICK_TRACKER. If true, select dynamic click trackers. If false, select static click trackers. Leave unset to select both.

parameters.description: Select only ads whose list targeting expression use these remarketing list IDs.

parameters.description: Allows searching for objects by name or ID. Wildcards (*) are allowed. For example, ad*2015 will return objects with names like ad June 2015, ad April 2015, or simply ad 2015. Most of the searches also add wildcards implicitly at the start and the end of the search string. For example, a search string of ad will match objects with name my ad, ad 2015, or simply ad.

get.description: Retrieves a list of change logs.

parameters.name: action
parameters.description: Select only change logs with the specified action.

parameters.name: ids
parameters.description: Select only change logs with these IDs.

parameters.name: maxChangeTime
parameters.description: Select only change logs whose change time is before the specified maxChangeTime.The time should be formatted as an RFC3339 date/time string. For example, for 10:54 PM on July 18th, 2015, in the America/New York time zone, the format is 2015-07-18T22:54:00-04:00. In other words, the year, month, day, the letter T, the hour (24-hour clock system), minute, second, and then the time zone offset.

parameters.name: maxResults
parameters.description: Maximum number of results to return.

parameters.name: minChangeTime
parameters.description: Select only change logs whose change time is before the specified minChangeTime.The time should be formatted as an RFC3339 date/time string. For example, for 10:54 PM on July 18th, 2015, in the America/New York time zone, the format is 2015-07-18T22:54:00-04:00. In other words, the year, month, day, the letter T, the hour (24-hour clock system), minute, second, and then the time zone offset.

parameters.name: objectIds
parameters.description: Select only change logs with these object IDs.

parameters.name: objectType

parameters.name: searchString
